        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philad.</placeName>
                <date>February 13/56</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><sic>Inclosed</sic> please find the article to be<lb/> inserted in
                your next <sic>occident</sic>, I find it all right, with the<lb/> exception of the
                circumstance as it <sic>happend</sic>, which you<lb/> will find below, so if you
                think proper or <sic>necessairy</sic> please attend.<lb/> If you wish to make any
                other alteration, or additions<lb/> I am satisfied, &amp; leave it to your good
                    <sic>judment</sic>, but<lb/> inserted I will have the affair.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain yours with respect</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">J H Carbstadter</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">Circumstance</hi>
            </p>
            <p>The gentlemen whom I send <del>dit</del>
                <sic>calld</sic> twice at the<lb/> ministers house, but <sic>dit</sic> not find him
                at home, therefore when<lb/> the Minyan were assembled, some one ask for the
                minister, the<lb/> gentlemen stated as above, consequently we <sic>comenced</sic>,
                some one<lb/> (not a minister) offered to read the service. Only after the
                minister<lb/> arrived we <sic>ascertaind</sic> that some one else had notified him
                of it,<lb/> which we assure the public <sic>dit</sic> not remember any more, of
                having<lb/> a day previous (on the day when we received the sad tidings) requested
                some<lb/> one else to notify the minister. The public will judge in what<lb/>
                situation we were in after receiving <add>?</add> news,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will please write the above correct, if you<lb/>
                <sic>dont</sic> find it so, &amp; change it as you think proper.<lb/> If you please
                    <add>?</add>
                <persName role="author">J. H.</persName> as I <sic>dont</sic> wish to make
                myself<lb/> to <sic>conspictious</sic> before the public, but if you think it
                    <sic>nessesaire</sic> to have the<lb/> name in full you may do it</p>
        </body>
